{
  "texts": [
    "To this end, as shown in the right-hand side of Figure 2, we design an Error Analyzer (EA) to extract error information from the above Execution Results (Step 8), including error lines and error messages.",
    "Taking the buggy Java program in Figure 5 as an example, Figure 6 is its Execution Result throwing a compilation error.",
    "Following our designed regular expressions, EA can extract the error line number (\"11\") and error message (\"cannot find symbol\") in Line 2, thereby providing necessary information in the TRP for program repair (highlighted in yellow).",
    "It should be noted that, as each translated program needs to be inserted into the testing template file (e.g., tmp.java and tmp.py, refer to [2] for details) for evaluation, \"11\" here is the buggy line number in tmp.java rather than in the translated program.",
    "Thus, we must subtract 6 prefix lines of our translated program (i.e., 11-6=5) in tmp.java."
  ]
}